                                                                                <h4>Bacula Conference 2010 Recap</h4>
                                                                                <p>The Bacula Conference in Yverdon, Switzerland, 27 and 28 
September 2010 was a great success - 2 packed days of Community 
presentations covering topics that ranged from BWeb Enterprise, 
dassModus configurator, Bacula's roadmap, Linux Bare Metal Recovery, 
Regression testing, Capabilities of the Storage Daemon, Bacula plugins, 
rpms and much more. All highly relevant, crucial subjects, and the 
ambience was great.</p>

<!--
<p><em>"We had a great time. The most interesting part was the discussion about 
the future of Bacula. To hear Kern talk about the future of Bacula makes 
us be able to plan our use of Bacula. "</em></p>                                <p align="right"><em><strong>Chryster, IT Architect</strong></em></p>
-->
                                                                                <p></p>
                                                                                <p>Overall, the conference proved to be a great place for 
giving feedback or ideas directly to the developers, learning more about
 Bacula and Bacula Systems, and hearing presentations about Bacula from 
the developers. Some folks talked together informally until pretty late 
on the Monday evening, and there was also a healthy general discussion 
on that Tuesday afternoon before the wrap-up.</p>
